cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.IR, cs.NE 

The paper deals with neural conversation models and their ability to generate contentful responses by incorporating external knowledge through on-demand machine reading. This involves natural language processing, machine learning, and information retrieval, which are all relevant to the sub-categories of cs.CL (Computation and Language), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.IR (Information Retrieval), and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Therefore, these are the most likely sub-categories for this paper.
